Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the deployment and connectivity behavior of the GameServer4g system:

```plantuml
@startuml jzyong_GameServer4g

participant Client
participant "Gateway (Gate)" as Gate
participant "Hall Server" as Hall
participant "World Server" as World
participant ZooKeeper
participant "Resource Server" as Resource
participant "Manager (HTTP)" as Manager

Client -> Gate : Connect (TCP)
Gate -> ZooKeeper : Register service
Hall -> ZooKeeper : Register service
World -> ZooKeeper : Register service
Resource -> ZooKeeper : Register service

Gate -> ZooKeeper : Discover Hall servers
Gate -> Hall : Connect (gRPC)
Hall -> ZooKeeper : Discover World servers
Hall -> World : Connect (gRPC)

Client -> Gate : Send game message
Gate -> Hall : Forward message (gRPC)
Hall -> World : Process game logic (gRPC)
World -> Hall : Send update (gRPC)
Hall -> Gate : Send response (gRPC)
Gate -> Client : Send response (TCP)

Manager -> ZooKeeper : Get service info
Manager -> Gate : Admin request (HTTP)
Manager -> Hall : Admin request (HTTP)
Manager -> World : Admin request (HTTP)
Manager -> Resource : Admin request (HTTP)

@enduml
```

This sequence diagram illustrates the deployment and connectivity behavior of the GameServer4g system, showing:

1. Client connection to the Gateway (Gate) using TCP.
2. Service registration with ZooKeeper for Gateway, Hall, World, and Resource servers.
3. Service discovery process using ZooKeeper.
4. Connections between Gateway and Hall, and Hall and World servers using gRPC.
5. Message flow from Client through Gateway, Hall, and World servers.
6. Admin requests from the Manager component to various services using HTTP.

The diagram represents the key components and their interactions, focusing on the deployment and connectivity aspects of the system.